data.title: twenty one pilots to launch ‘Clancy’ world tour

data.text:
Twenty One Pilots announced they will hit the road for its 59-date ‘The Clancy World Tour’ in support of their upcoming album, Clancy. The duo of Tyler Joseph and Josh Dun posted on social media: ‘The Clancy World Tour is bringing us back to see so many of you. |-/ Get info and presale access here: twentyonepilots.com/tour’

The 59-date tour kicks off Aug. 15 at the Ball Arena in Denver, Colo. with stops in Seattle, Phoenix, New York City, Los Angeles, Chicago and their hometown of Columbus, Ohio before wrapping up the North American leg on Oct. 12 at Target Center in Minneapolis, Minn. The international leg of the tour begins in Auckland, New Zealand, on Nov. 17 and will make stops in Australia the rest of the month. The tour resumes April 2025 in Germany, Italy, Spain, France and more before wrapping up with two shows at London’s 02 Arena on May 13 and 14.

The band also dropped the video for “Next Semester,” the second single from Clancy. The music video — directed by Andrew Donoho — kicks off with the band perfomring in a tiny, packed club; take a look at the video for “Next Semester” – here.

Presale tickets are available now, with general on sale beginning April 5 at 10 a.m. local time via Ticketmaster. More information about the tour and tickets can be found on Twenty One Pilots’ website.
